article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- — Ray'Sean Taylor's 30 points led SIU-Edwardsville past Western Michigan 79-60 on Friday night. Taylor added seven assists for the Cougars (3-2). Desmond Polk scored 16 points while going 7 of 14 (2 for 7 from 3-point range). Brian Taylor II shot 4 for 6, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with 10 points. Owen Lobsinger led the Broncos (1-3) in scoring, finishing with 16 points. The score was 43-29 at halftime. Ray'Sean Taylor scored 17 points in the second half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
